article.description: — Keith Williams had 27 points as Cincinnati edged past Furman 78-73 on Wednesday.
article.headline: Williams scores 27 to lead Cincinnati over Furman 78-73
article.linkText: Williams scores 27 to lead Cincinnati over Furman 78-73
article.story: CINCINNATI -- — Keith Williams had 27 points as Cincinnati edged past Furman 78-73 on Wednesday. Chris Vogt had four assists for Cincinnati (2-1). David DeJulius added nine rebounds. Clay Mounce had 23 points for the Paladins (4-1), whose four-game season-opening winning streak was snapped. Noah Gurley added 20 points and eight rebounds, and Mike Bothwell had 14 points, six rebounds and six assists. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
